"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. One of the things I hear the most about uh trying to save the world through my backyard garden is uh yeah, but no one's gonna do that, and you have eight billion people to feed, so we're just gonna keep doing things the way we're doing it, and uh yeah, what do you have to say about that? No, nothing. That's the way it is. I'm really not trying to save the world, I'm trying to save my neighborhood. I'm trying to create a small community, and the people that are interested will be interested. I'd love to hear from y'all. If you're in the Houston area and you're interested in forming a gardening community based on living soils and composting, I'll drop off barrels of compost to you and uh I'll actually buy your vegetables later and sell them at the farmer's market. I need more. Uh but you know, other than that, like that's that's really what I'm trying to do. I'm trying to very form a very small community of people who care. Everybody else who who doesn't have the time to do this, who doesn't care to do this, um that's fine. You know, I I think that when things really fall apart, and they are, I'm convinced of it now, uh, and food becomes scarce and water becomes difficult to get, and it good water becomes difficult to get, then you know, the people who prepared for it will be the people who prepared for it, and everybody else will just be everybody else. And you know, we're not trying to save out eight billion people, we're not trying to keep the world going the way it is. It's not going to. We can't stop that. This is a runaway train. You know, someone jumping in front of this. There's no stopping this. All we can do is try to figure out a way to protect ourselves here on the ground and live a life that's worth living, uh, despite what may go on with these crazy people who are running everything. So there it is, you know, eight billion people. No, I c my backyard garden it's gonna fall short. But you know, if a bunch of us do it in the community and sell it to farmers market, maybe we could form kind of a little spine going through our community uh that could protect us a little bit as as things fall down. Because right now we're just a bunch of loose bones if even that. We have no structure whatsoever. We all completely rely on the man in the supermarkets and all the other things are so fragile. Uh so anyway, you know, I'm gonna try to reach out to my community and see who at the farmers market, maybe they they got a nephew who's kinda idle and needs something to do. Hey, what about gorilla gardening? I'll set you up. Let's go. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 5.04,\n      \"end\": 6.48,\n      \"duration\": 1.44,\n      \"confidence\": 0.982,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 5.04,\n          \"end\": 5.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.98\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 5.28,\n          \"end\": 5.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 5.52,\n          \"end\": 5.68,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 5.68,\n          \"end\": 6.0,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 6.0,\n          \"end\": 6.16,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 6.16,\n          \"end\": 6.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.914\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \" One of the things I hear the most about uh trying to save the world through my backyard garden is uh yeah, but no one's go